summary: This is an email chain between FBI personnel discussing logistics for assisting potential victims of Jeffrey Epstein. The emails coordinate meeting locations and times for victim interviews scheduled in West Palm Beach, Florida, on July 11, 2019.

persons.name: M.S.C.J.
persons.context: FBI Victim Specialist based in Miami and Homestead Resident Agency, whose contact information is included in the email signature block.

events.title: Epstein Victim Interviews in West Palm Beach
events.description: FBI personnel coordinate logistics for meeting with and assisting potential victims of Jeffrey Epstein, with interviews scheduled at 11 AM and 3 PM.

keyFacts: FBI personnel were coordinating victim assistance related to the Jeffrey Epstein case in July 2019.
Interviews with potential victims were scheduled for July 11, 2019, in West Palm Beach, Florida.
The email chain shows operational planning between FBI offices (NY and Miami) regarding victim services.
The correspondence indicates the FBI was actively engaging with potential victims following renewed investigation into Epstein.
